  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This unit evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The intended use scope — predicting normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) within ±15% under steady-state VAD operating conditions (flow 3–6 L/min, pressure rise 60–120 mmHg) — is described in the bound requirement and claim prose. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed; 7 show achieved levels below required levels, 6 are flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo UQ was performed. Decision: Accepted under residual-risk acknowledgement pending corrective action plan.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cou2-vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-cfd-hemolysis-vad-class3",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v2",
